The present technical cooperation project aims to:
- Consolidate pedagogical, curricular and educational management practices;
- Diagnoses, research and good pedagogical practices identification;
- Develop pedagogical material for all day education;
- Improve pedagogical and curricular practices;
- Develop training material for education professionals;
- Develop tools, methodologies and diagnoses to support the pedagogical management of the Secretariat;
- Identify innovative technologies, content and educational methodologies;
- Improve the Secretariat's educational programs management capacity.

Subsequent to an intervention with the COHSOD on Education in 2018 on Comprehensive Sexuality Education (CSE) in HFLE, UNFPA along with its partners executed a High Level Policy Dialogue (HLPD) on CSE in HFLE.  The Dialogue facilitated agreement on 36 recommendations (annexed) under the thematic areas of: Policy and Governance (7); Monitoring and Evaluation (3); Knowledge Management and Strategic Information (4); Multi-sectoral, Inter-sectoral and Community Collaborations (3) and Capacity building and Programme Implementation (19).
 
One of the key follow up arrangements agreed at the HLPD was the implementation of a follow up meeting of HFLE Technocrats to review and operationalize the recommendations proffered.  In light of this, UNFPA in collaboration with CARICOM, PANCAP, UNESCO, UNAIDS, UNICEF and PAHO is pursuing the implementation of this follow up meeting in Trinidad and Tobago on June 26 and 27, 2019. This will be a technical meeting which will focus on the reprioritization of the recommendations agreed and the development of an operation plan for their implementation.  The main objectives of this meeting may be articulated as follows:
1. To facilitate technical exchange on good practices and know how between Caribbean governments implementing CSE and HFLE;
2. To agree on key strategies and approaches for operationalizing selected recommendation on advancing CSE in HFLE;
3. To develop indicative work-plan to improve the delivery of CSE in HFLE.

